---
title: Herbed Chicken Over Apple & Kale Salad with Parmesan, Dried Cranberries & Dijon Dressing
description: Step aside, mixed greens—this hearty kale salad is the stuff of dinner dreams. You’ll toss kale with crisp, refreshing apple slices and Parmesan cheese in a creamy, tangy honey Dijon dressing. Top it all with garlic-herb seared chicken cutlets and sprinkle with dried cranberries for chewy-sweet textural contrast.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/661d6aeb3d20ae432f30b5ed-58091b97.jpeg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/661d6aeb3d20ae432f30b5ed-en-US.pdf
course: main course
cuisine: North America
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/herbed-chicken-over-apple-kale-salad-661d6aeb3d20ae432f30b5ed
author: Sara Heilman
nutrition:
  calories: 530 kcal
  fat: 26 g
  saturated fat: 5 g
  carbohydrates: 34 g
  sugar: 25 g
  protein: 38 g
  fiber: 5 g
  sodium: 500 mg
servings: 2
time required: 20 minutes
---

Wash and dry produce.

Remove and discard any large stems from @kale{4%ounce}; chop into bite-size pieces. Halve, core, and thinly slice @apple{1}.

Place kale in a #large bowl{}; using your hands, massage kale with a large drizzle of @olive oil{3%teaspoon} (similar to how you would knead dough) until leaves are tender, ~{1-2%minutes}.

> Don't skip the massaging step—massaging helps the kale leaves wilt slightly, lending a tender (never fibrous!) texture.

Pat @chicken cutlets{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}; place between two large pieces of #plastic wrap{}. Pound with a #mallet{} or #rolling pin{} until chicken is about 1⁄2 inch thick. Season all over with @garlic powder{1%teaspoon}, half the @dried thyme{1%teaspoon}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%teaspoon} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add chicken; cook until browned and cooked through, ~{3-5%minutes} per side.

Transfer to a #cutting board{}.

Meanwhile, in a #small bowl{}, whisk together @honey Dijon dressing{1.5%ounce}, @Dijon mustard{2%teaspoon}, and a drizzle of olive oil. Season lightly with salt and pepper.

Slice chicken crosswise.

Add apple and @parmesan cheese{3%tablespoon} to bowl with kale. Toss with as much dressing as you like.

Divide salad between bowls. Sprinkle with @dried cranberries{1%ounce}. Top with chicken. Drizzle with any remaining dressing. Serve.

> Chicken is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.